<BaseLayout title="Corrections & Suggestions" description="Report a correction or suggest a practical Dama Korea guide through our public issue tracker."><section class="page-hero"><div class="shell"><span class="eyebrow">Corrections</span><h1>Help us keep the details useful.</h1><p>We use a public issue tracker so readers can see what was reported and when it was addressed.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="article-shell article-body"><div class="quick-answer"><strong>Open a public report</strong><a href="https://github.com/huynjuunn-glitch/Milo/issues/new" rel="external">Create a correction or guide suggestion on GitHub →</a></div><h2>For a correction</h2><ul class="checklist"><li>Include the URL of the page.</li><li>Quote the sentence or section that may be wrong.</li><li>Explain what changed and when you observed it.</li><li>Include an official source when available.</li></ul><h2>For a guide suggestion</h2><p>Describe the practical problem, who encounters it and what existing guides fail to explain. We prioritize topics that affect international visitors or residents and can be verified responsibly.</p><h2>Privacy</h2><p>The tracker is public. Never post passport details, residence numbers, addresses, banking records, private screenshots or other personal information. A GitHub account may be required to submit a report.</p></div></section></BaseLayout>
